The paper discusses natural language interfaces to database systems, which falls under the intersection of natural language processing (NLP) and database management systems (DBMS). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for validation and verification of data and queries, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses information extraction and structured information in free text, which falls under information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the challenges in achieving expressive and effective translations, which involves language generation (LG), making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
